00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,400
You get a guy that
that many people

787
00:39:59,433 --> 00:40:00,567
got a motive for killing,

788
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:02,433
you either get lucky
or you either get slow.

789
00:40:02,467 --> 00:40:03,367
- Yeah.

790
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:06,333
Well, we're working the
David West angle.

791
00:40:09,333 --> 00:40:10,200
- David West.

792
00:40:13,300 --> 00:40:14,167
Good luck, Posey.

793
00:40:15,400 --> 00:40:17,667
I spent a long time trying
to break that alibi.

794
00:40:17,700 --> 00:40:21,100
- Yeah, well, we've
got a girl next to him.

795
00:40:21,133 --> 00:40:22,600
Her name's Kim Paris.

796
00:40:22,633 --> 00:40:24,500
She's, well...

797
00:40:24,533 --> 00:40:25,533
Well, she's kind of flaky,

798
00:40:25,567 --> 00:40:27,633
but she's got her
hooks into West.

799
00:40:27,667 --> 00:40:30,433
The only thing is, Clyde
doesn't take her seriously.

800
00:40:31,667 --> 00:40:33,033
- So?

801
00:40:33,067 --> 00:40:35,200
- Well, you know the case.

802
00:40:35,233 --> 00:40:36,100
You know West.

803
00:40:36,133 --> 00:40:37,133
I thought maybe you
could talk to her

804
00:40:37,167 --> 00:40:39,733
and see if you could
figure out what she's got.

805
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:45,400
She's kind of exposed out there.

806
00:40:48,300 --> 00:40:49,367
- What's in it for me?

807
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:53,533
- Apple pie.

808
00:40:55,767 --> 00:40:56,667
- A la mode?

809
00:40:58,233 --> 00:40:59,233
- One scoop.

810
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:01,400
- One scoop.

811
00:41:02,633 --> 00:41:04,033
All right, bring her by.

812
00:41:04,067 --> 00:41:04,433
- All right.

813
00:41:04,467 --> 00:41:05,467
Louise?

814
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:06,667
- Okay, now I recommended
you with the agency.

815
00:41:06,700 --> 00:41:08,533
You're gonna have to tell me
if you're getting anywhere.

816
00:41:08,567 --> 00:41:09,067
- Listen, listen.

817
00:41:09,100 --> 00:41:09,933
I got a great idea.

818
00:41:09,967 --> 00:41:10,800
David is a believer in
psychic stuff.

819
00:41:10,833 --> 00:41:11,500
Cindy was psychic.

820
00:41:11,533 --> 00:41:12,433
- Nevermind about the psychic.

821
00:41:12,467 --> 00:41:13,267
Just tell me if you're
getting anyplace.

822
00:41:13,300 --> 00:41:14,400
- Will you just listen to me,
Tom?

823
00:41:14,433 --> 00:41:17,467
Okay, I'm gonna tell David
that I've had this dream,

824
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:19,033
like he's in danger, you know?

825
00:41:19,067 --> 00:41:20,700
And then the next time
that I go and pick him up,

826
00:41:20,733 --> 00:41:22,400
you drive by and you fire a gun.

827
00:41:22,433 --> 00:41:24,500
Not at us, but I mean
like in the air, okay?

828
00:41:24,533 --> 00:41:27,000
And then he'll think I
have it, really have it.

829
00:41:28,133 --> 00:41:28,767
- This is crazy.

830
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:29,333
This is...

831
00:41:29,367 --> 00:41:30,333
This is really crazy.

832
00:41:30,367 --> 00:41:32,500
You didn't put this in
your report, did you?

833
00:41:32,533 --> 00:41:33,633
- Hey, it was just an idea.

834
00:41:33,667 --> 00:41:35,433
I'm just trying to be creative.

835
00:41:35,467 --> 00:41:36,833
- It sounds like you're
desperate to me.

836
00:41:36,867 --> 00:41:38,433
- Maybe I should be taping it.

837
00:41:39,333 --> 00:41:40,300
(horn honks)

838
00:41:40,333 --> 00:41:41,167
- Theresa.

839
00:41:41,200 --> 00:41:42,700
- David.

840
00:41:42,733 --> 00:41:44,200
It's David.

841
00:41:44,233 --> 00:41:46,500
You play along with me,
all right?

842
00:41:46,533 --> 00:41:47,433
Hi.

843
00:41:47,467 --> 00:41:48,600
- How are you?

844
00:41:50,567 --> 00:41:51,667
Hey, look at you.

845
00:41:51,700 --> 00:41:52,567
- I look awful.

846
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:54,467
- You do not.

847
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:56,400
- This is my
brother-in-law Sonny.

848
00:41:58,367 --> 00:41:59,400
- Well, hello, Sonny.

849
00:42:00,333 --> 00:42:01,800
Theresa told me about you.

850
00:42:01,833 --> 00:42:02,667
- Oh, yeah?

851
00:42:02,700 --> 00:42:03,767
Yeah, she mentioned you.

852
00:42:05,333 --> 00:42:06,200
- Great.

853
00:42:08,100 --> 00:42:09,667
Hey, how about you and your
wife having dinner some night

854
00:42:09,700 --> 00:42:11,533
with me and Theresa
over at my place?

855
00:42:11,567 --> 00:42:13,500
- Oh, Sammi would love that.

856
00:42:13,533 --> 00:42:15,700
You know how she loves to
go out, Sonny.

857
00:42:17,300 --> 00:42:19,700
- I fix a pretty good
Mongolian lamb.

858
00:42:19,733 --> 00:42:21,367
How about Saturday?

859
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,133
- Saturday?

860
00:42:22,167 --> 00:42:22,933
Uh.

861
00:42:22,967 --> 00:42:24,200
- I think Saturday
would be fine.

862
00:42:24,233 --> 00:42:25,467
- [Tom] I don't know.

863
00:42:25,500 --> 00:42:26,667
- [Kim] I'll work on him.

864
00:42:26,700 --> 00:42:28,167
- Saturday.

865
00:42:28,200 --> 00:42:29,067
Hey.

866
00:42:33,633 --> 00:42:35,267
Well, good.

867
00:42:35,300 --> 00:42:36,167
Nice to meet you.

868
00:42:37,133 --> 00:42:38,167
Saturday it is.

869
00:42:41,233 --> 00:42:44,400
(engine starts)

870
00:42:44,433 --> 00:42:46,100
- [Kim] Bye, David!

871
00:42:46,133 --> 00:42:47,500
See you Saturday!

872
00:42:49,500 --> 00:42:51,100
- Damn it, you are careless,
Kim.

873
00:42:51,133 --> 00:42:52,333
We should not have
been out here.

874
00:42:52,367 --> 00:42:55,167
- I thought that worked
out pretty good, Sonny.

875
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:56,633
- What is this
brother-in-law crap?

876
00:42:56,667 --> 00:42:59,100
- That's what I told him why I
can't invite him to my house.

877
00:42:59,133 --> 00:43:01,033
I live with this pig of
a brother-in-law Sonny.

878
00:43:01,067 --> 00:43:01,600
You'll be perfect, huh?

879
00:43:01,633 --> 00:43:02,467
- No, no.

880
00:43:02,500 --> 00:43:04,133
No, I am absolutely not
going to dinner

881
00:43:04,167 --> 00:43:05,300
pretending to be some hood.

882
00:43:05,333 --> 00:43:06,733
- You gonna blow my cover, Tom?

883
00:43:06,767 --> 00:43:07,700
Is that what you want, huh?

884
00:43:07,733 --> 00:43:10,367
If I tell Clyde that
you can't pull it off,

885
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:13,067
he won't let you fetch
his cigarettes anymore.

886
00:43:13,100 --> 00:43:14,300
(Kim laughs)

887
00:43:14,333 --> 00:43:15,200
- [Tom] Kim.

888
00:43:16,733 --> 00:43:17,667
- Don't forget, Sammi.

889
00:43:17,700 --> 00:43:19,133
You're different when
you're around Sonny.

890
00:43:19,167 --> 00:43:21,467
You're quiet, subdued.

891
00:43:21,500 --> 00:43:22,633
- Where'd you come up
with this mafia?

892
00:43:22,667 --> 00:43:23,867
What was the idea of that?

893
00:43:23,900 --> 00:43:26,033
- Well, didn't you say that
the Campbell murders were like,

894
00:43:26,067 --> 00:43:28,267
you know, executions,
like professional?

895
00:43:28,300 --> 00:43:29,400
- Yeah.

896
00:43:29,433 --> 00:43:31,533
- Okay, so maybe Cindy had
somebody hire some hitmen.

897
00:43:31,567 --> 00:43:33,367
Maybe David is the one who
did the hiring.

898
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:34,433
Did you ever think of that?

899
00:43:34,467 --> 00:43:35,300
- This is crazy.

900
00:43:35,333 --> 00:43:36,100
It's absolutely crazy.

901
00:43:36,133 --> 00:43:36,633
Crazy, Kim.

902
00:43:36,667 --> 00:43:37,567
- Theresa, Theresa.

903
00:43:37,600 --> 00:43:38,800
You gotta remember to
call her Theresa.

904
00:43:38,833 --> 00:43:42,533
- Hey, would you watch your
mouth when you're talking to me?

905
00:43:42,567 --> 00:43:44,467
You're gonna end up
with cement shoes.

906
00:43:46,167 --> 00:43:47,800
(laughing)

907
00:43:47,833 --> 00:43:49,367
- This is never gonna work, Kim.

908
00:43:49,400 --> 00:43:50,233
I mean, Theresa.

909
00:43:50,267 --> 00:43:51,633
This is never gonna work.

910
00:43:51,667 --> 00:43:54,233
(laughs) No.

911
00:43:54,267 --> 00:43:55,533
- I don't believe in free will.

912
00:43:55,567 --> 00:43:57,400
I mean, it looks like you
have a choice,

913
00:43:57,433 --> 00:43:59,300
but when you examine,
really examine it,

914
00:43:59,333 --> 00:44:01,633
you see one thing leads to
another the only way it could've.

915
00:44:01,667 --> 00:44:03,500
I mean, all history's inevitable

916
00:44:04,733 --> 00:44:07,200
'cause it goes through
the trouble of happening.

917
00:44:07,233 --> 00:44:08,533
May sound kind of fatalist.

918
00:44:08,567 --> 00:44:09,533
- [Tom] Sounds dumb.

919
00:44:12,267 --> 00:44:13,400
That's what it sounds like.

920
00:44:13,433 --> 00:44:15,567
- You believe in free will then?

921
00:44:15,600 --> 00:44:18,667
- Oh, nothing's free,
including this dinner.

922
00:44:18,700 --> 00:44:19,833
- Now, what price do
you see yourself

923
00:44:19,867 --> 00:44:22,133
paying for this dinner?

924
00:44:22,167 --> 00:44:23,800
- Well, I gotta sit here
and listen to you go on

925
00:44:23,833 --> 00:44:26,100
about all this stuff you
don't know nothing about.

926
00:44:30,067 --> 00:44:32,200
Why don't you two broads
go powder something?

927
00:44:32,233 --> 00:44:33,567
- [Sammi] Sonny.

928
00:44:33,600 --> 00:44:35,533
- [Tom] Go on, beat it.

929
00:44:49,767 --> 00:44:52,067
- You certainly have a way
with the ladies, Sonny.

930
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,600
- West, don't use
sarcasm with me.

931
00:44:54,633 --> 00:44:56,233
It ain't gonna work.

932
00:44:57,533 --> 00:44:59,700
What I want to know
about is what you

933
00:44:59,733 --> 00:45:01,500
have in mind with my
sister-in-law.

934
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:04,600
- I intend to marry Theresa.

935
00:45:06,500 --> 00:45:08,367
I respect your position,
your feelings,

936
00:45:08,400 --> 00:45:10,700
and how you're
protective about her,

937
00:45:10,733 --> 00:45:12,633
but I'm gonna take care of her.

938
00:45:12,667 --> 00:45:14,500
Now, this house is my
property and I can fix it up

939
00:45:14,533 --> 00:45:15,533
and get a very good price.

940
00:45:16,800 --> 00:45:19,100
Theresa and me didn't have any
choice but to meet each other

941
00:45:19,133 --> 00:45:22,367
and we have no choice but to
keep on knowing each other.

942
00:45:22,400 --> 00:45:25,133
I don't know how it is
with you and Sammi,

943
00:45:25,167 --> 00:45:27,133
but that's how it is with
Theresa and me.

944
00:45:33,833 --> 00:45:35,533
- We'll be out in the car, okay?

945
00:45:35,567 --> 00:45:36,667
Oh, and thank you, David.

946
00:45:36,700 --> 00:45:37,567
Goodnight.

947
00:45:40,067 --> 00:45:41,733
Theresa will join us
in a moment.

948
00:45:44,533 --> 00:45:45,733
That guy's nuts.

949
00:45:45,767 --> 00:45:47,200
He did it, I really
think he did it.

950
00:45:47,233 --> 00:45:47,533
- Uh-uh.

951
00:45:47,567 --> 00:45:48,167
No way.

952
00:45:48,200 --> 00:45:49,267
- What do you mean no way?

953
00:45:49,300 --> 00:45:51,433
- Oh, he's out to lunch all
right, but not that way.

954
00:45:51,467 --> 00:45:52,500
Want to know what he told me?

955
00:45:52,533 --> 00:45:53,067
- What?

956
00:45:53,100 --> 00:45:53,800
- He wants to marry her.

957
00:45:53,833 --> 00:45:54,533
- Oh, my god.

958
00:45:54,567 --> 00:45:55,400
- Oh, yeah.

959
00:45:55,433 --> 00:45:56,233
You wanna know what else?

960
00:45:56,267 --> 00:45:57,133
- What?

961
00:45:57,167 --> 00:45:58,267
- They have no choice, he says.

962
00:45:58,300 --> 00:45:58,700
- What?

963
00:45:58,733 --> 00:45:59,667
- No choice.

964
00:46:02,433 --> 00:46:07,267
- David, shouldn't you
have asked, well,

965
00:46:07,300 --> 00:46:09,633
spoken to me before you
spoke to him?

966
00:46:09,667 --> 00:46:12,067
- I don't think I did
anything wrong.

967
00:46:12,100 --> 00:46:13,400
I love you, Theresa.

968
00:46:13,433 --> 00:46:15,700
- I know, but what I'm saying
is shouldn't you have--

969
00:46:15,733 --> 00:46:16,700
- Do you?

970
00:46:16,733 --> 00:46:17,700
Do you really know?

971
00:46:18,700 --> 00:46:20,700
Do you really know I love you?

972
00:46:20,733 --> 00:46:22,067
I wanna marry you.

973
00:46:23,467 --> 00:46:24,800
When I have to, I can
get things done.

974
00:46:24,833 --> 00:46:27,067
I do not intend to
deliver blueprints

975
00:46:27,100 --> 00:46:28,700
for the rest of my life.

976
00:46:28,733 --> 00:46:30,533
Take this house, fix it up,
and sell it.

977
00:46:30,567 --> 00:46:32,600
We can do whatever we
want to do with the money.

978
00:46:32,633 --> 00:46:35,400
Have a life, family.

979
00:46:36,733 --> 00:46:37,600
You and me.

980
00:46:42,367 --> 00:46:45,100
(water rushing)

981
00:46:58,567 --> 00:47:01,433
- He asked me to marry him,
Sammi.

982
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:07,633
Isn't that something?

983
00:47:09,100 --> 00:47:11,000
I mean, a lot of guys
have hit on me,

984
00:47:12,400 --> 00:47:16,300
but the first time I get the
white picket fence proposal

985
00:47:16,333 --> 00:47:18,133
and I'm pretending to be
somebody else.

986
00:47:19,367 --> 00:47:22,233
- Kim, why don't you just
forget this whole thing?

987
00:47:23,533 --> 00:47:26,333
- What, tell him I changed
my name to Kim Paris

988
00:47:26,367 --> 00:47:28,267
and you got divorced from Sonny?

989
00:47:28,300 --> 00:47:30,567
- You don't have to
tell him anything.

990
00:47:30,600 --> 00:47:32,233
Not a thing.

991
00:47:32,267 --> 00:47:33,800
We could just split.

992
00:47:33,833 --> 00:47:35,767
I'm not exactly
doing great here.

993
00:47:39,667 --> 00:47:40,533
- Mm-mm.

994
00:47:42,200 --> 00:47:45,233
- You're getting serious about
this guy, aren't you, Kim?

995
00:47:48,533 --> 00:47:51,833
Aren't you?

996
00:47:51,867 --> 00:47:52,533
- Kim isn't.

997
00:47:52,567 --> 00:47:54,633
I'm not so sure about Theresa.

998
00:48:04,233 --> 00:48:07,367
(people chattering)

999
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:08,267
Excuse me.

1000
00:48:13,067 --> 00:48:13,733
Watch it.

1001
00:48:27,067 --> 00:48:29,600
(metal banging)

1002
00:48:30,733 --> 00:48:32,333
Do you know where
Sergeant Halsey is?

1003
00:48:32,367 --> 00:48:33,500
Halsey.

1004
00:48:33,533 --> 00:48:36,400
- Halsey, he's banging on
that typewriter over there.

1005
00:48:36,433 --> 00:48:37,267
That's right.

1006
00:48:37,300 --> 00:48:38,133
You're quite welcome.

1007
00:48:39,167 --> 00:48:40,267
- [Dan] Piece of junk.

1008
00:48:45,233 --> 00:48:48,667
- Sergeant Halsey, Kim Paris
from the Clyde Wilson Agency.

1009
00:48:49,733 --> 00:48:51,667
How do you want me, sitting,
standing?

1010
00:48:53,533 --> 00:48:55,367
- I don't know if I
want you at all.

1011
00:48:57,733 --> 00:48:59,300
All right, all right.

1012
00:48:59,333 --> 00:49:00,667
What do you got on David West?

1013
00:49:01,833 --> 00:49:04,267
- I think he knows a
lot about Cindy Campbell

1014
00:49:04,300 --> 00:49:05,500
and about her parents.

1015
00:49:07,100 --> 00:49:09,100
- Well, no kidding.

1016
00:49:10,367 --> 00:49:12,500
That couldn't be because
he was shacked up with her

1017
00:49:12,533 --> 00:49:14,033
for two years, now could it?

1018
00:49:15,667 --> 00:49:19,033
- He lied to me about the way
the Campbells were killed.

1019
00:49:19,067 --> 00:49:20,700
He said they were
better people dead.

1020
00:49:20,733 --> 00:49:22,133
- Did he tell you who shot 'em?

1021
00:49:22,167 --> 00:49:23,033
- [Kim] No.

1022
00:49:23,067 --> 00:49:24,267
No, he didn't say
anything like that.

1023
00:49:24,300 --> 00:49:25,233
- Well, what do you think?

1024
00:49:25,267 --> 00:49:26,167
What do you think?

1025
00:49:26,200 --> 00:49:26,867
- Me?

1026
00:49:26,900 --> 00:49:28,700
- Yeah, you, Miss Private Eye.

1027
00:49:28,733 --> 00:49:31,533
What is your
professional opinion?

1028
00:49:32,500 --> 00:49:33,300
- I don't know.

1029
00:49:33,333 --> 00:49:34,733
I don't think that David.

1030
00:49:34,767 --> 00:49:36,700
- Well, let me ask you this.

1031
00:49:36,733 --> 00:49:39,200
How long have you been
shacked up with David West?

1032
00:49:43,200 --> 00:49:45,300
- I'm not shacked up
with David West.

1033
00:49:45,333 --> 00:49:47,467
- I hear tell that he
wants to marry you.

1034
00:49:47,500 --> 00:49:50,033
Now, why would a weirdo
like David West

1035
00:49:50,067 --> 00:49:52,333
want to marry you, Ms. Paris?

1036
00:49:52,367 --> 00:49:53,500
- I think he's in love with me.

1037
00:49:53,533 --> 00:49:54,367
- Oh, in love.

1038
00:49:54,400 --> 00:49:55,433
Oh, well sure.

1039
00:49:55,467 --> 00:49:56,233
Now, I see.

1040
00:49:57,533 --> 00:50:00,600
In order to prove his
love to you,

1041
00:50:00,633 --> 00:50:02,600
he's gonna confess to
the Campbell murders.

1042
00:50:02,633 --> 00:50:03,500
Is that it?

1043
00:50:04,400 --> 00:50:05,067
Okay.

1044
00:50:05,100 --> 00:50:06,167
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

1045
00:50:06,200 --> 00:50:07,333
